commit.message: Bump version number to 4.2.6
Add test case for multistream bzip2 reading

Fix issue where bzip2 files containing multiple streams were being truncated

Thanks to Bill Herrin for pointing this out (#54)
Merge branch 'develop'
Bump version to 4.2.5

http: configure curl to abort "idle" connections

Threshold for idleness is set to under 100B/s for 60 seconds.

Prior to this change, idle connections could leave a wandio http
reader "hanging", when the better alternative is to simply kill
the connection and try again.
Update package building scripts for latest distros
Merge branch 'develop'
Invoke lsb_release AFTER installing the package for it...
Deal with lack of debhelper 12 in default bionic repository
Force use of latest cloudsmith upload actions
Replace bintray with cloudsmith in run-tests.sh

Remove unneeded macros in configure.ac

These were introduced by an autoupdate, but they do not
exist in older versions of autoconf anyway so were causing
errors when trying to build on older Ubuntu/Debians...

Preparation for 4.2.4 release

 * bump version numbers
 * update packaging changelogs
 * update maintainer info for post-WAND world
 * update package building actions
Add timestamp to "HTTP ERROR" error messages
Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/develop' into develop
Remove deprecated behaviour from configure scripts
Fix broken compression method detection from output file names

Add LIBTRACEIO option for suppressing certain HTTP errors

In some contexts, the server resetting the connection can
happen with some regularity and is usually resolved by simply
retrying the HTTP download.

Also added a timestamp to all "HTTP ERROR" messages.
